How to start after shutting down:

1. Open Sublime text app. Click file and open web server folder.

2. Open terminal:
  (base) hafizah@Hafizahs-iMac ~ % cd Desktop
  (base) hafizah@Hafizahs-iMac Desktop % . web\ server/bin/activate
  (web server) (base) hafizah@Hafizahs-iMac Desktop % cd web\ server
  (web server) (base) hafizah@Hafizahs-iMac web server % export FLASK_ENV=development
  (web server) (base) hafizah@Hafizahs-iMac web server % export FLASK_APP=server.py
  (web server) (base) hafizah@Hafizahs-iMac web server %  python3 -m flask run
  * Serving Flask app "server.py" (lazy loading)
  * Environment: development
  * Debug mode: on
  server
  * Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000/ (Press CTRL+C to quit)
  * Restarting with stat
  server
  * Debugger is active!
  * Debugger PIN: 241-380-545
  
3. Copy http://127.0.0.1:5000/ on browser and see website.

4. After finish, stop server : (Press CTRL+C to quit)

5. Before closing terminal : type "deactivate" then "exit"


